function add(a, b) {    // parameter 
  return a + b;
}

const result = add(3, 5); // 3 and 5 are arguments passed to the function

Parameters are defined in the function declaration and act as placeholders for values.
Arguments are the actual values that are passed to the function when it's called.
Parameters and arguments are closely related. The values of arguments are assigned to the corresponding parameters when the function is executed.
